Document: using_gridmaps
Path: godot/tutorials/3d/using_gridmaps.rst
Summary: Introduces GridMaps as a tool for creating 3D levels using a collection of 3D meshes placed on a grid, similar to 2D TileMaps.

GridMaps are a tool for creating 3D game levels, similar to the way TileMap works in 2D. You start with a predefined collection of 3D meshes (a MeshLibrary) that can be placed on a grid, as if you were building a level with an unlimited amount of Lego blocks. Collisions and navigation can also be added to the meshes, just like you would do with the tiles of a tilemap.
---CHUNK---
